ume."],"quality_gate":["Route is correct without coach rescue.","Final stop or turn is balanced with no extra hop unless the drill calls for a run-through.","Knee tracks over toes on the plant leg.","Athlete can repeat the same shape on both sides.","Speed increases only after control is repeatable."],"stop_signs":["Pain in ankle, knee, hip, back, or groin.","Slipping surface or cones sliding into the athlete path.","Repeated uncontrolled knee valgus or trunk collapse.","Athlete cannot remember route or react safely.","Fatigue changes braking mechanics."]}'::jsonb,
